# Environment Variables for Render Deployment

Copy these to your Render.com service:

## Required Variables

```bash
# Telegram Configuration
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=<your_telegram_bot_token>
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=<your_telegram_chat_id>

# Cloudflare D1 Configuration
CF_ACCOUNT_ID=573f9a28fb2a48c7c065c9fe6223429b
D1_DATABASE_ID=2318c943-7efd-4dd5-97c1-36039621be59
CF_API_TOKEN=<create_new_token_with_d1_edit_permission>
```

## Notes

1. **TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN**: Get from @BotFather on Telegram
2. **TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID**: Your channel or group chat ID
3. **CF_API_TOKEN**: ⚠️ Create NEW token with **D1 Edit** permission
   - See [D1_PERMISSIONS_FIX.md](file:///C:/Users/oshada/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/baiscope-scraper/D1_PERMISSIONS_FIX.md) for instructions
   - Your current token has limited permissions

## Deployment Checklist

- [ ] Create new Cloudflare API token with D1 Edit permission
- [ ] Add all environment variables to Render
- [ ] Deploy service to Render
- [ ] Visit `https://your-app.onrender.com/` to verify it's running
- [ ] Visit `https://your-app.onrender.com/scrape/subz` ONCE for initial population
- [ ] Monitor logs in Render dashboard
- [ ] Check `/status` endpoint for statistics

